HEADWORD: Portmote
<hw>Port"mote`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>In old English law,
a court, or mote, held in a port town.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
